---
import BlockOffLayout from '../../layouts/BlockOffLayout.astro';
---

<BlockOffLayout
  title="About Us | Block OFF"
  description="Learn about Block OFF, an AI comment moderation product built to help creators protect YouTube and Instagram communities."
  canonicalPath="/blockoff/about"
>
  <header class="site-header page-header">
    <a class="brand" href="/blockoff" aria-label="Block OFF home"><img src="/blockoff/block-off-logo.png" alt="" /><span>Block OFF</span></a>
    <nav class="main-nav" aria-label="Primary navigation"><a href="/blockoff/#product">Product</a><a href="/blockoff/#how">How it works</a><a href="/blockoff/#dashboard">Dashboard</a><a href="/blockoff/#pricing">Pricing</a></nav>
    <a class="header-cta" href="/blockoff/#pricing">Try now</a>
  </header>
  <main>
    <section class="page-hero">
      <span class="section-kicker">About</span>
      <h1>Creators should not need to babysit the worst comments online.</h1>
      <p>Block OFF exists to protect creator energy, brand safety, and community quality without forcing people to manually inspect every reply.</p>
    </section>
    <section class="legal-layout">
      <nav class="legal-nav" aria-label="About sections"><a href="#mission">Mission</a><a href="#why">Why now</a><a href="#mvp">MVP focus</a><a href="#values">Values</a></nav>
      <article class="legal-content">
        <section id="mission"><h2>Our mission</h2><p>Block OFF is being built as a practical AI comment moderation tool for YouTube and Instagram creators. The mission is simple: help creators keep publishing without letting scam links, harassment, hate, and spam dominate their community.</p><p>We believe social media tools should protect the people doing the work. A creator should be able to launch a video, reel, campaign, or product without spending the next few hours removing obvious abuse by hand.</p></section>
        <section id="why"><h2>Why now</h2><p>Comment sections move faster than manual moderation. As creators grow, every post can attract bots, impersonators, rage comments, and harmful replies. Teams with money can hire moderators. Smaller creators need a lighter and more affordable shield.</p><p>AI moderation is finally good enough to help with the repetitive first pass: scan, classify, hide risky comments, and send uncertain cases into review.</p></section>
        <section id="mvp"><h2>MVP focus</h2><p>The first version focuses on YouTube and Instagram because those platforms are where creators most often need public comment protection. The dashboard will prioritize scanned comments, hidden comments, restored comments, top triggers, and account health.</p></section>
        <section id="values"><h2>Product values</h2><ul><li>Creators stay in control of their own moderation rules.</li><li>Hiding and review should come before permanent deletion.</li><li>Useful criticism should not be treated the same as abuse.</li><li>Every automated action should be visible and reversible.</li></ul></section>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>
  <footer class="site-footer">
    <a class="brand footer-brand" href="/blockoff" aria-label="Block OFF home"><img src="/blockoff/block-off-logo.png" alt="" /><span>Block OFF</span></a>
    <nav aria-label="Footer navigation"><a href="/blockoff/privacy">Privacy Policy</a><a href="/blockoff/terms">Terms & Conditions</a><a href="/blockoff/returns">Returns & Refunds</a><a href="/blockoff/about">About Us</a><a href="/blockoff/contact">Contact Us</a><a href="/blockoff/support">Support</a><a href="/blockoff/changelog">Changelog</a></nav>
  </footer>
</BlockOffLayout>
